<h2>NATIONAL FRAUD INFORMATION CENTER</h2>
<h3>A Project of National Consumers League</h3>
<hr>
<p><strong>Editor's note:</strong> This information is provided as a service to our visitors by The Alexander Law Firm. 
Should you wish to visit the National Fraud Information Center, you may do so by choosing <a href="http://www.fraud.org">this link</a> (http://www.fraud.org).</p>
<hr>
<p>The National Fraud Information Center, a project of National Consumers League, is working to combat the growing menace of 
fraud. The Center provides information, referral services, and assistance in filing complaints. It gives professionals involved in 
consumer fraud prevention and law enforcement access to advanced communications and data systems. The result is improved 
regulation, prevention, apprehension, and enforcement.</p>
<p>A recent U.S. Government-sponsored study reports that consumer fraud takes a $40 billion annual toll on its victims. A recent 
Louis Harris Survey, conducted for the National Consumers League, found that 92 per cent of adult Americans are affected.</p>
<p>The National Fraud Information Center provides a variety of services for consumers and consumer protection professionals: a 
toll-free Consumer Assistance Service; FraudNet communications, network, and referral services for enforcement, regulatory, 
and fraud prevention agencies; and NFIC F.A.S.T. (FraudNet Alert System), a state of the art data network, message service, 
and information center.</p>
<h4 align=center>National Fraud Information Center<br>
CONSUMER ASSISTANCE<br>
1-800-876-7060</h4>
<p>The National Fraud Information Center toll-free Consumer Assistance Service provides:</p>
<p>* Accurate Information on how and where to report fraud</p>
<p>Victims no longer waste time contacting agencies or organizations which cannot help them</p>
<p>* Direct complaint referral to the Federal Trade Commission's National Telemarketing Fraud Database</p>
<p>Fraud reports are available to law enforcement authorities instantly</p>
<p>* Good advice for consumers</p>
<p>A friendly voice for older Americans and others who need someone to talk to when they are contacted about fabulous offers and 
irresistible opportunities. An invaluable service for anyone who has questions about a telephone or mail solicitation.</p>
<p>The National Fraud Information Center Consumer Assistance Service is available nationwide from 9:00 a.m. to 5:30 p.m., 
Eastern Time, Monday through Friday. TDD service for the deaf and other special needs services available during normal office 
hours.</p>
<h4>Se Habla Espanol</h4>
<p>NFIC is a project of The National Consumers League, America's oldest private, non-profit national consumer organization, and 
represents a major step forward in the League's long term commitment to curtail consumer fraud. Founding corporate sponsors 
of the National Fraud Information Center are Citibank, Master Card/Visa, MCI Communications Corporation, MasterCard 
International, and VISA USA. American Telephone and Telegraph (AT&amp;T) became a corporate sponsor in 1993. Additional 
support has been received from Federal Express.</p>
<p>NFIC does not disclose to any non-governmental organization the identity of individuals filing reports or reporting incidents. 
NFIC does not provide evaluation reports on specific businesses or comment as to their reliability.</p>
<ul>
<li>NFIC Agency Referral Line (202) 783-0967<br>
Consumer Assistance (800) 876-7060<br>
Facsimile (202) 347-0646<p>P. O. Box 65868<br>
Washington, D.C. 20035<br>
</p>
</li>
</ul>
