<h4>Check-Up Visits</h4>
<p>Your child's doctor or other health care provider may want to see your child for check-up visits even when shots or test are not 
due. Some authorities recommend check-up visits at the following ages: 2-4 weeks; 2, 4, 6, 9, 12, 15 and 18 months; and 2, 3, 
4, 5, 6, 8, 10, 12, 14, 16 and 18 years. Your child's doctor or other health cam provider will discuss with you increasing or 
decreasing the number of these visits to meet the individual needs of your child.</p>
<p>My Child's Check-Up Schedule:<br>
(Record age and/or date)<br>
