electric blankets as well as the newer model PTC (Positive Temperature Coefficient) Low Magnetic Field blankets. The fields 
were measured at a distance of five centimeters (a little less than 2 inches) from the surface of the blanket, roughly approximating 
the distance from the blanket to the users' internal organs. Because of the way blankets are wired, magnetic field strengths vary 
from point to point on the blanket. The graph reflects this and gives you both the peak as well as the average measurement.</p>
