<a href="../article/adoption.shtml"><img src="../adopted.gif" alt="[Problem Adopted Children]" align=bottom border=0 width=142 height=33></a> <a href="../article/seizures.shtml"><img src="../seizures.gif" alt="[Seizures in Asthmatic Children]" align=bottom border=0 width=142 height=33></a></p>
<h3><a href="../index.html">The Consumer Law Page</a>: <a href="index.html">Brochures</a>:</h3>
<hr>
</body>

</html>
</p>
<h3>The Bureau of the PUBLIC DEBT</h3>
<h2>Treasury Investors..... Make the Smart Exchange</h2>
<p>Do you still hold Treasury securities in paper form? If you do, you may be taking the unnecessary risk that your securities could 
be lost, stolen, or destroyed.</p>
<p>You can reduce these risks by joining millions of other Treasury investors in making the Smart Exchange from paper Treasury 
certificates to a book-entry account. Book-entry accounts provide a number of benefits which make investing in Treasury 
securities a safer and easier decision than ever before. These benefits include:</p>
<h4>Safety</h4>
<p>* Since book-entry accounts are paper-less, there is no risk that your Treasury securities could be lost, stolen, or destroyed.</p>
<p>* With a book-entry account, your holdings are safely kept on account at the U.S. Treasury, a financial institution, or a 
brokerage house.</p>
<h4>Convenience</h4>
<p>* With a book-entry account, the interest and maturity payments for your Treasury securities are credited to your account 
automatically on the payment date. You don't need to go to a financial institution or Federal Reserve Bank to cash checks, clip 
coupons, or redeem matured certificates.</p>
<p>* In most cases, information about your Treasury account is immediately available to you at the time of an inquiry, regardless of 
where your account is established. You can also review the status of your holdings at home simply by reviewing your statement 
of account.</p>
<p>Many investors have switched from paper Treasury investments to book-entry. Now it's your turn to experience the advantages 
of book-entry Treasuries.</p>
<h4>Now It's Your Turn...</h4>
<p>The first step in exchanging your Treasury securities for a book-entry account is to choose the book-entry system that is best for 
you. Your choice of systems should be based on how active you want to be in the management of your Treasury securities 
portfolio.</p>
<p>The Treasury offers two types of book-entry systems:</p>
<p>* Commercial book-entry, offered through financial institutions and brokers; and</p>
<p>* TREASURY DIRECT, offered by the U.S. Treasury's Bureau of the Public Debt.</p>
<h4>Commercial Book-Entry</h4>
<p>Commercial book-entry, available through most financial institutions and brokers, may be most appropriate if you want a third 
party to manage your account, or if you plan to sell your securities prior to maturity. In the commercial book-entry system, your 
account records are maintained on the books of the third party you select. Interest and maturity payments are made directly to 
the third party who disburses the funds to your account. These third parties may charge a fee for the services they provide.</p>
<h4>TREASURY DIRECT</h4>
<p>TREASURY DIRECT, the Department of the Treasury's automated book&#169;entry system, is ideal if you plan to keep your 
securities from the purchase to maturity, and if you wish to manage your own account. Securities held in a TREASURY 
DIRECT account are maintained directly on the records of the Bureau of the Public Debt. Since 1986, all new issues of Treasury 
bills, notes, and bonds have been issued only in book-entry form.</p>
<p>TREASURY DIRECT offers you the following benefits:</p>
<p>* TREASURY DIRECT is offered free of charge at Federal Reserve offices throughout the country.</p>
<p>* All interest and maturity payments are deposited on time and automatically into an account of your choice through direct 
deposit. Direct deposit eliminates the possibility of destroyed, lost, or stolen checks.</p>
<p>* TREASURY DIRECT provides a single master account for all Treasury securities holdings having the same registration, 
simplifying your record-keeping. You are mailed a statement of account after any transaction or change that affects your master 
account, including reinvestments.</p>
<p>* With TREASURY DIRECT, you have the option of reinvesting in other Treasury securities being offered at the same time your 
current holdings mature. Now that you know about the different book-entry systems available, it's time to exchange the paper 
securities you've been holding for a book-entry account. You Know It Makes Sense The sooner you exchange your Treasury 
securities for a book-entry account, the sooner you will enjoy the benefits that book-entry systems offer. So, make the Smart 
Exchange. You'll have peace of mind knowing your Treasury investments are safer and more convenient than ever.</p>
<p>Call the Smart Exchange today.<br>
1 (800) 366-3144</p>
<p>A Smart Exchange kit will be mailed to you immediately.<br>
PD P-012 </p>
