</TD><TD align=middle rowspan=2><IMG SRC="flags.jpg" WIDTH=158 HEIGHT=192 ></TD></TR>
</TABLE>
</CENTER>
 




<UL>
<CENTER><FONT SIZE=+3><EM><STRONG>Who is the AACI?</STRONG></EM></FONT></CENTER><HR WIDTH=60% ALIGN=center><P>

<FONT SIZE=+1>
<FONT SIZE=+2>AACI, </FONT>the Association of Americans & Canadians in Israel, is a volunteer organization with headquarters in Jerusalem. We are thousands of North American Olim; all of us have made Israel our home.<P>

<FONT SIZE=+2>AACI</FONT> has served North American Olim for over 40 years.
 Established in 1951 as the first "self help" immigrant organization in 
Israel, AACI is a unique and integral part of the Israeli absorption system. 
Serving some 50,000 adult members currently in
 Israel and a further 3,000 newcomers yearly, AACI acts as advocate for 
the entire North American Community in Israel. <P>


<FONT SIZE=+2>AACI's</FONT> varied range of activities reflects our 
cost-effective, efficient operation. We offer the most comprehensive 
absorption assistance in Israel, maintaining a staff of professional 
counselors across the country. These counselors provide expert 
information and guidance on <A HREF="employ.htm">employment</A>, 
<A HREF="apartmnt.htm">housing</A>, culture shock, 
<A HREF="timetabl.htm"> oleh rights</A>, customs & shipping,  
<A HREF="ben&serv.htm#Education"> education</A> & <A HREF="adventur.htm"> adventures in learning</A>, 
<A HREF="volunt.htm#aaci">volunteerism </A> and 
<A HREF="ben&serv.htm"> other information</A>. They also arrange
 <A HREF="sprogram.htm"></A> Events for Seniors
 and <A HREF="youth.htm"></A> Young Olim.  <P>

<FONT SIZE=+2>V</FONT>olunteers and Lay-Leaders are at the heart of 
AACI's effectiveness. We have developed a comprehensive system which 
helps Olim help each other. Volunteers meet new 
Olim at the airport, welcome them into their homes and help them 
find their way through the bureaucratic maze. Our Lay/Professional 
structure nurtures a participatory democracy. The 
partnership of professional staff and active volunteers carry out 
the policies set by membership.<P>

<FONT SIZE=+2>W</FONT>e are a true service organization in the best 
North American traditions. Our emphasis is on Volunteerism, 
Professionalism and dynamic Zionism. Through our efforts towards 
successful absorption and retention of Olim, we serve as a beacon for increased Aliyah and a stronger Israel.
</UL></FONT>
<CENTER>
 <TABLE BORDER=2 CELLPADDING=2 CELLSPACING=2>
<TR><TD>
