<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>AACI - Post Aliyah Timetable</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="bgrnd.jpg" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#0000FF" VLINK="#800080" ALINK="#FF0000">
<IMG SRC="logo-sm.gif" WIDTH=394 HEIGHT=48><HR>
<UL>
<CENTER><FONT SIZE=+3><EM><STRONG>Post Aliyah Timetable for New Olim</STRONG></EM></FONT></CENTER><HR WIDTH=70% ALIGN=center><P>
<STRONG>This is a schedule of deadlines which newcomers should keep in 
mind.  Please remember that, as with other generalized information, 
there are exceptions, and sometimes changes.  Before any action, speak to 
an AACI counselor.</STRONG><P>
</UL>
<CENTER>
<TABLE BORDER=3 CELLPADDING=5 CELLSPACING=0>
<TR><TH>Amount of Time</TH><TH>Visa Status</TH><TH>Deadline In Israel</TH></TR>
<TR><TD>45 days</TD><TD>Olim & TR</TD>
<TD>Deposit all cash & travelers checks in bank.</TD></TR>

<TR><TD>3 months</TD><TD>Olim only</TD>
<TD>Automatic acquisition of Israeli citizenship</TD></TR>

<TR><TD>Within 3 months</TD><TD>Olim & TR</TD>
<TD>Upon passing practical driving exam, exchange foreign license for Israeli one in order to drive LEGALLY IN ISRAEL.</TD></TR>


<TR><TD>6 months</TD><TD>Olim only</TD>
<TD>During the first 6 months of Aliyah Olim are exempt from paying 
health tax provided that their income is not higher than 5% of 
the average pay, or if they are unemployed. If olim receive a living 
allowance they are entitled to 12 months free.</TD></TR>

<TR><TD>Within 1st year</TD>
<TD>Olim & TR</TD><TD>Receive free AACI membership of up to 3 months.</TD></TR>

<TR><TD>1 1/2 years = 18 months</TD>
<TD>Olim & TR</TD><TD>End of first period of income tax reduction, 
3 additional credit points.</TD></TR>

<TR><TD>After another 12 months = 2 1/2 years</TD><TD>Olim & TR</TD>
<TD>End of second period of income tax reduction, 2 additional 
credit points.</TD></TR>

<TR><TD>Within 3 years</TD>
<TD>Olim & TR</TD>
<TD>Upon passing practical driving exam, exchange foreign license 
for Israeli one. (if you wait  beyond this period you will be required to take several driving lessons and pass more intensive tests.)</TD></TR>

<TR><TD>3 years</TD><TD>Olim & TR</TD>
<TD>End of reduced customs period  for cars.</TD></TR>

<TR><TD>3 years</TD><TD>Olim & TR</TD>
<TD>End of full customs-free period for other goods.</TD></TR>

<TR><TD>3 years</TD><TD>TR</TD>
<TD>Generally end of Temporary Residence Status.</TD></TR>

<TR><TD>After another 12 months = 3 1/2 years</TD><TD>Olim & TR</TD>
<TD>End of third and final period of income tax reduction, 
1 additional credit  point.</TD></TR>

<TR><TD>5 years</TD><TD>Olim only</TD>
<TD>End of period of Oleh rental subsidies.</TD></TR>

<TR><TD>5 years</TD><TD>Olim only</TD>
<TD>End of Ministry of Absorption business loans</TD></TR>

<TR><TD>7 years</TD><TD>Olim & TR</TD>
<TD>End of Israel income tax exemption on passive income from abroad 
which is received directly in Israel.</TD></TR>

<TR><TD>7 years</TD><TD>Olim & TR</TD>
<TD>End of partial exemption of payment of real estate transfer 
fee - Land Registry Office (<I>"Mas Rechisha"</I>). 0.5% on an apartment under NIS900,000  4.5% on any amount over NIS900,000 </TD></TR>

<TR><TD>7 years</TD><TD>Olim only</TD>
<TD>End of period for Oleh mortgages.</TD></TR>

<TR><TD>20 years</TD><TD>Olim & TR</TD>
<TD>End of tax free period on interest on foreign 
currency accounts in Israel. End of export of foreign currency.</TD></TR>

<TR><TD>30 years</TD><TD>Olim & TR</TD>
<TD>End of free foreign currency holding privileges.</TD></TR>
</TABLE></CENTER><P>
