<html>
<head><title>AACI - Adventures in Learning</title></head>
<body BACKGROUND="bgrnd.jpg" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#0000FF" VLINK="#800080" ALINK="#FF0000">
<IMG SRC="logo-sm.gif" WIDTH=394 HEIGHT=48><hr>
    <h1>The Continuing Education Program</h1>          <H3> Adventures in Learning</H3>
Adventures in learning called STUDY VACATIONS are a  significant and 
impressive part of AACI's programming for both new and veteran Olim.<BR> Under 
the Continuing Education Committee of AACI, the Study Vacation program is 
entering its second decade and has attracted over 2000 AACI members from 
all parts of Israel, since its inception in February 1986. <P>The short term 
educational experience of three or four days is open to all ages. Lectures, 
tours and "hands-on" activities combine to provide participants with a 
unique learning experience through which they discover new and exciting 
facets of Israel, understand better its problems, explore its history and 
geography and, in the bargain, meet and make new friends. <BR>Topics covered in 
the past have included archaeology; ecology and the environment; political, 
social and economic issues and challenges; arts and culture; and 
technological advances and discoveries.

                        <H3>Coming Study Vacations   1996 - 1997</H3>

<I><B>October 14-17/1996</B> </I><BR>     Ethnic Communities in the Negev, visiting       
                Ethiopian and Cochin Indian Jews, and the Bedouin       
                with accommodation in BeerSheva at the Bet Yatziv       
                Guest House.<P>

<I><B>November 18-20/1996 </B></I><BR>    Tales of Tel Aviv, bus & walking tours of Jaffa, 
                        old and modern Tel Aviv, and hands on activities at 
                        the Eretz Yisrael Museum in coordination with the 
                        museum. Accommodations at the Grand Deborah Hotel 
on                      Ben Yehuda St. Tel Aviv.
<P>
<B><I>February 3-6/1997</I></B><BR>       Behind the Headlines, Myths & realities of Israeli 
                        Society - Families in distress, Forgotten Children 
                        and Change in Development Towns. Accommodation at 
                        Kibbutz Gal-On near Kiryat Gat.
<P>
<B><I>March 31 - April 3/1997</I></B><BR> Beit Shean Through The Ages: Exploring the Beit 
                        Shean Valley, Afula and Mt. Gilboa region.      
                        Accommodation at Kibbutz Shluchot near Beit Shean.
<P>
        <H3>The Study Vacation program is open to all English -speakers,    
including tourists.</H3>For details contact Chaim or Norma:<BR> Sundays and     
Wednesdays 10:30 - 1:30 <BR>at the National Office of AACI, <BR>
        Telephone 02-661181<BR> Fax 02-661186 <BR>or write to 
        Continuing Education<BR> AACI Head Office,<BR>
 POB 4337 Jerusalem 91042
<p><p>
