<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>AACI - Central Region</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="bgrnd.jpg" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#0000FF" VLINK="#800080" ALINK="#FF0000">
<IMG SRC="logo.gif" WIDTH=299 HEIGHT=104><HR>
<UL>
<CENTER><FONT SIZE=+7>
<EM><STRONG>Central Region</STRONG></EM></FONT></CENTER>
<HR WIDTH=60% ALIGN=center>
<FONT SIZE=+1>T</FONT>he Central Region of the AACI spans from Ashdod 
(south) to Rishpon (north) and Arielle (east) to the Mediterranean coast.  
It included the major population areas of Tel Aviv, Rehovot, Holon, 
Rishon L'Zion, Petach Tikva, Ramat Gan, Bnei Brak, Savyon, Ramat Aviv, 
Herzliya, Herzliya Pituach, Ramat Hasharon, Ra'anana, Kfar Saba, 
Hod Hasharon, Koav Yair, Kfar Shmaryahu.<P>

<FONT SIZE=+1>O</FONT>ur office, located in downtown Tel Aviv, is 
the coordinating hub for a variety of services, ranging from general 
information about aliyah and absorption to concrete assistance in 
finding jobs and housing.  As the financial center of the country, 
the Tel Aviv office of AACI sponsors Networking programs geared 
to English-speaking professionals which are known for their success 
in helping North Americans build both business and social contacts 
in the area.<P>

<FONT SIZE=+1>O</FONT>ur unique services and support to olim include:<P>
<UL TYPE=square>
<LH></LH>
<LI>Professional and Business Networks
<LI>Professional Women's Network
<LI>Business After Hours
<LI>Supports and social group for North Americans Married to Israelis
<LI><A HREF="yes.htm">Young English speakers (Y.E.S.)</A>
<LI>Pazazz.  An independent activity group for the 20's to 40's set.
<LI>Widow and Widowers Group
<LI>Single Groups
<LI>Mother and Baby Groups
<LI>A variety of courses and workshops in English
<LI>"Way Off Broadway" Music Theater Group
<LI>Financial Education Seminars
</UL><P>
<FONT SIZE=+1>T</FONT>hese activities are located in Tel Aviv and in 
the various other Central region cities as requested and developed by 
AACI members.<P>

<FONT SIZE=+1>C</FONT>entral region presents its members with many 
opportunities to become actively involved in AACI and Israel through 
a wide range of volunteer activities, particularly satisfying to our 
member's professional abilities.
</UL><P>
<A HREF="taevents.htm"></A><IMG SRC="bult.jpg" WIDTH=22 HEIGHT=22  ALIGN=texttop BORDER=0> Schedule of 
Events in the Central Region<P>
</UL>


