<HEAD>
<TITLE>AACI - Southern Region</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="bgrnd.jpg" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#0000FF" VLINK="#800080" ALINK="#FF0000">
<IMG SRC="logo.gif" WIDTH=299 HEIGHT=104><HR>
<CENTER><FONT SIZE=+7><EM><STRONG>Southern Region</STRONG></EM></FONT></CENTER><HR WIDTH=60% ALIGN=center>
<H3>SHALOM YA'ALL!!!</H3> WELCOME TO THE SOUTHERN REGION OF AACI.  WE 
HAVE JUST MOVED TO NEW AND IMPROVED QUARTERS, IT IS BRIGHT, 
SHINY AND SUNNY, WITH WINDOWS THAT LOOK OUT ON BEAUTIFUL 
LAWN AND FLOWERS.  <P>THE MANY VOLUNTEERS WHO HELPED RENOVATE 
THE BUILDING, PACKED THE OLD OFFICE AND MOVED US INTO THE NEW 
ONE, SHOWS THE INTEREST THAT IS ALIVE IN THE SOUTH AND WHY IT IS 
SO IMPORTANT FOR US TO BE A FACTOR THERE. <BR> IT IS EASY AND 
CONVENIENT TO REACH AND OUR MEMBERSHIP HAS BEEN FLOCKING TO 
IT SINCE WE OPENED ONE MONTH AGO.  
<P>
	IN ADDITION TO THE REGULAR SERVICES LISTED IN THE AACI 
BROCHURE, OUR SENIORS HAVE AN ACTIVE BRANCH AND RUN TRIPS ON 
A MONTHLY BASIS WHICH ARE VERY POPULAR AND GETTING MORE SO 
ALL THE TIME. <BR> OUR NEW PROGRAM CHAIRMAN HAS SCHEDULED A 
SERIES OF COFFEE HOUSES WITH PROGRAMS ON VARIOUS TOPICS OF 
INTEREST TO ALL,  IN FACT WE JUST HAD THE FIRST ONE, THE SUBJECT 
BEING "INTERNET".<BR> WE HAD AN OFFICE FILLED WITH PEOPLE 
INTERESTED.  OUR BULLETIN HAS UNDERGONE MANY CHANGES AND 
WILL CONTINUE TO CHANGE AND GROW AS OUR NEW BULLETIN EDITOR 
FINDS HER WAY. <BR> SHE IS EXCITED AND INTERESTED AND COMES DOWN 
EVERY 3-4 MONTHS AND THEIR SCHEDULE IS FULL EVERY TIME, 
INDICATING THE NEED AND DESIRE FOR HAVING THESE TYPES OF 
SERVICES AVAILABLE LOCALLY FOR OUR MEMBERSHIP.  <P>WE HAVE 
VOLUNTEERS MANNING THE OFFICE EVERY DAY SO THAT KATRINA CAN 
BE FREE TO DO ALL THE THINGS NECESSARY TO THE RUNNING OF THE 
REGION WITHOUT THE WORRY OF TELEPHONES, MAIL, ETC.
COME ON DOWN AND SEE US SOME TIME.  <P>WE ARE ANXIOUS TO 
GREET YOU AND SHOW YOU THE RE-VITALIZED SOUTHERN REGION.  YOU 
ARE WELCOME ANY TIME. <P> SEE YA'ALL SOON.
<P>
SHALOM,
<P>
AHUVAH<BR>
CHAIRMAN, SOUTHERN REGION

<H3>WHAT'S HAPPENING IN THE SOUTHERN REGION </H3>
<I><B>TELEVISION PRODUCTION COURSE</B></I>
<P>
A course in television production is now being offered in English through AACI  and 
ED Productions. <BR> THE COURSE LOCATION WILL BE IN BEER SHEVA AND 
INCLUDES THE FOLLOWING:
<BR>
*	8 months of supervised production work
<BR>
*	Additional production work and special topics covered as the year proceeds.
<P>
If  you are interested and required further information, <BR>please call Janet Levy (07-
467486) or Katrina at the office (07-230688). <BR> All applicants will be interviewed by ED 
Productions <BR>prior to the commencement of the course. <BR> No previous experience is 
required to be accepted.  <BR>(Minimum of 10 participants required).
<HR><p>
<b><i>ULPAN FOR VATIKIM - EVENING CLASSES</i></b>
<p>
HOW'S  Your Hebrew?  <BR>Can you go to the Makolet and make yourself understood but 
have problems expressing your thoughts in Hebrew?  <BR>do you find it difficult writing a 
letter and reading the newspaper?  <BR>	AACI and the Mercaz Klita in "Hey", BEER 
SHEVA are interested in starting up an evening class. <BR> For further details please contact 
Katrina at the office (07-230688) by 30.4.96
<hr><p>
<b><i>JUDAISM IN ENGLISH</i><b>
<p>
It's an intellectual, psychological and fun discussion of the Torah and Midrash.  <BR>No 
homework, <BR>no heavy religious discussion, <BR>just some enjoyable and often entertaining 
enlightenment.  <BR>To join us call Zev at 371261. <BR> PROGRAM LOCATED IN EILAT


	


