<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>AACI - Tips for Olim</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="bgrnd.jpg" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#0000FF" VLINK="#800080" ALINK="#FF0000">
<IMG SRC="logo-sm.gif" WIDTH=394 HEIGHT=48><HR>
<UL>
<CENTER><FONT SIZE=+3><EM><STRONG>Standard Tips for Encounters with Bureaucracy</STRONG></EM></FONT></CENTER><HR WIDTH=60% ALIGN=center><P>
<UL TYPE=disc>
<LH></LH>
<LI>Always bring your Teudat Oleh and Teudat Zehut.<P>
<LI>Bring original documents when possible, but never give these originals 
to anyone. Have photocopies to submit with files and applications 
when necessary.<P>

<LI>Bring photographs.

<LI>Always carry some "significant" cash as you never know when you 
will need to pay a fee.<P>

<LI>It is preferable to call ahead in advance to find out what 
documents to bring, with whom you need to speak, if there is a 
fee, etc.  You can save hours of unnecessary waiting by calling first.  
Be sure to clarify the hours that the office is open to receive 
the public.<P>
<LI>Make sure your information is complete.  A good question to ask 
is "what else do I need to bring?"<P>
<LI>Always get the name of the clerk with whom you are speaking.  
It's also a good idea to get their phone/extension number so 
you can get back to them easily if any problem arises.<P>
<LI>Be patient and keep calm.  Many clerks are willing to explain 
and be helpful to you, but obviously communication is a two-way 
street and they are responding to you.  A smile and friendly attitude 
on your part can go a long way!<P>
<LI>For discounts and benefits always carry your AACI membership card.<P>
</UL>
</UL>
<BOTTOMINSERT>
<CENTER>
<A HREF="http://www.jer1.co.il/cgi-bin/imagemap/aacimap"><IMG 
SRC="botmbutn.gif" border=0 ISMAP></A><P>

