<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>AACI - Airport Information </TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="bgrnd.jpg" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#0000FF" VLINK="#800080" ALINK="#FF0000">
<IMG SRC="logo-sm.gif" WIDTH=394 HEIGHT=48><HR>
<UL>
<CENTER><FONT SIZE=+3><EM><STRONG>
AACI AIRPORT INFORMATION SHEET
</STRONG></EM></FONT></CENTER>


<P><A HREF="#before">JUST BEFORE  YOU LEAVE  ON ALIYAH....</A><BR>
<A HREF="#after">AND AT  BEN GURION AIRPORT AFTER YOU ARRIVE....</A><br>
<A HREF="#extra">EXTRA INFORMATION FOR YOU...</A><br></P>

<A NAME="before"></A>
<P><B>Information for Olim just before Aliyah</B></P>

<P>1.	Please make sure you have all the documents you need readily available for processing at Misrad HaKlita at the airport in Israel:
<UL>
<LI>Passport(s) for each member of the family.
<LI>Visa(s) if this a separate document.  These are for Passport Control
	when you land.
</UL>

<A NAME="after"></A>
<P><B>At the Ben Gurion Airport after arrival in Israel - </B><BR>
The Aliyah Processing- For Olim</P>

<P>1.	Please look for an AACI representative who is waiting for you as you get off the bus and enter the building for incoming passengers.  This person is there to welcome you and to take you through the processing procedure at Misrad HaKlita.  The AACI representative will be holding an AACI sign.</P>

<P>2.	If you do not find an AACI representative, please present your passport and visa at the Passport Control window and state that you are a new oleh.  Your passport will then be stamped correctly, and you will be told where to proceed next (Misrad HaKlita).</P>

<P>3.	At Misrad HaKlita, please submit the rest of your documents:
<UL>
<LI>Request for Aliyah (the form with your picture attached).
<LI>Summary of Processing form from the Aliyah Center.
</UL></P>

<P>4.	You will receive three (3) documents:
<UL>
<LI>A referral form for health insurance coverage.  You will select one of the four (4) Sick Funds (Kupot Cholim).   Go to the Kupat Cholim office and register soon after Aliyah.  This should be done as soon after your arrival as possible. 
<LI>Application for your permanent identity card (Teudat Zehut).  Make sure that all your details listed, are correct.  Soon after Aliyah, go to the Ministry of Interior with two pictures, your Teudat Oleh,  and all your other documents.  Children under 16 are listed in the parent's Teudah.  At age 16, each child can receive his/her own Teudat Zehut.  If you wish to Hebraicize your name or correct spelling, this is the office where it is done.
<LI>Teudat Oleh.  This document verifies your status as a new oleh, and you will need this document for any and all rights and privileges as you apply for them.  It will be required when you release your shipments, for purchase of household electrical appliances without import tax, for purchase of a car at reduced import tax and for use of Klita rights etc.  Check to see that all your details listed inside are correct.
</UL>
</P>

<P>5.	After processing, your AACI representative will get your travel voucher and take you downstairs to collect your luggage.  Computers and Lap Tops will be taxed (17-19% as of August 1996), unless you have arranged the necessary documentation stating that this is part of your business equipment.  This can  be arranged only after Aliyah.  See AACI information sheet titled: Olim Import of Equipment for a Business. </P>

<P>6.	Your AACI representative will then take you outside and arrange for your transportation to your destination.  The trip is paid for,  but it is customary to tip the driver who loads and unloads your baggage.</P>



<A NAME="extra"></A>
<P>PLEASE NOTE:
<OL TYPE=1, 2, 3, ...>
<LI>There is a nursery for you to care for infants (changing diapers, nursing etc.)
<LI>All food and refreshments are kosher in accordance with the law concerning government offices.
<LI>You are entitled to make a phone call within Israel, courtesy of Bezek.
<LI>You are entitled to make an overseas call, courtesy of Bezek.  If you wish to do this, please have the phone number ready.
</OL>
</P>


<P>Note: If you are a katin hozer, yalid hul, or temporary resident, ( A -1 ), you are entitled to free transport from the airport to your destination, but you do not get processed at the airport.  Go to the local branch of the Ministry of Interior and Absorption in your area.</P>

<P>  This information has been compiled by AACI Klita Chairperson and Airport
  Volunteer, Lynn Davison, and edited by Cindy Breakstone, AACI 
  Coordinator of Klita Services.  - August 1996</P>


<P>

