<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>AACI - Ulpan List</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="bgrnd.jpg" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#0000FF" VLINK="#800080" ALINK="#FF0000">
<IMG SRC="logo-sm.gif" WIDTH=394 HEIGHT=48><HR>
<UL>
<CENTER><FONT SIZE=+3><EM><STRONG>ULPANIM 1996</STRONG></EM></FONT></CENTER><HR WIDTH=60% ALIGN=center><P>
<FONT SIZE=+1>I</FONT>t is up to the oleh to register for an ulpan.  Information on the various ulpanim can be received at the regional AACI offices.  There are intensive Ulpanim 
run by the government or municipalities which generally run Sundays through 
Thursdays, from 8 or 8:30am to 12:30 or 13:00pm.  ....The Ministry of Absorption will 
often provide a subsidy for studies in one of the intensive Ulpanim.  Check with your 
local Ministry of Absorption to see if you will be eligible to receive this subsidy and 
tuition free, and whether or not you will be entitled to enroll.  Generally speaking, an 
Oleh needs to be within his first year in Israel to get this subsidy.  Many of the 
Absorption Centers offer an Ulpan.  There are also some private intensive Ulpanim in 
various cities where you may not be eligible for the subsidy.<P>
 
<FONT SIZE=+1>N</FONT>on-intensive Ulpanim are mostly run in the mornings, afternoons, or evening 2 to 3 
times a week depending on the individual Ulpan.  No living subsidy is available for 
attending them, the individual Ulpanim may offer tuition discounts for olim.   These 
Ulpanim can either be private or municipally/government run.  Although no living 
subsidy can be received while studying in an non-intensive Ulpan, often olim, who have 
found a job right away, attend the non-intensive evening Ulpanim in order to be able to 
work at the same time.<P>

<FONT SIZE=+1>I</FONT>ntensive and non-intensive Ulpanim may have a set time of year when they begin new 
classes, but often many of them accept people on a rolling admissions.<P>
 </UL>
<H1>Index</H1>
<FONT SIZE=+1>
<A HREF="#Jerusalem Region">Jerusalem Region Ulpanim</A><BR>
<A HREF="#Central Region">Central Region Ulpanim</A><BR>
<A HREF="#Five Town Ulpanim">Five Town Ulpanim</A> (Caesaria, Hadera, Zichron Yaakov, Karkur, Pardes Chana, Binyamina)<BR>
<A HREF="#Rechovot Ulpanim">Rechovot Ulpanim</A><BR>
