<FONT SIZE=+2><STRONG><A NAME="Five Town Ulpanim">Five Town Ulpanim</A>:<BR>Caesaria, Hadera, Zichron Yaakov, Karkur, Pardes Chana, Binyamina</STRONG></FONT><P>
<FONT SIZE=+1>T</FONT>here had been ulpanim in Zichron and Binyamina 
under the aegis of the Ulpan Director in Pardes Chana, Tel: 06-6378707.  Pardes Chana 
Ulpan sometimes hold Ulpan Bet and evening Ulpanim. <BR>
This fluctuates according to demand.  For information about Ulpanim, please contact 
the Municipal Klita Department or the Ministry of Absorption in Hadera.  Depending on 
demand, counselors, ("metaplot") of the Ministry of Absorption receive olim to assist 
them with information.  The same applies for Zichron and Pardes Chana.  However, these 
"metaplot" generally speak Hebrew and Russian.<P>

<FONT SIZE=+2><STRONG><A NAME="Rechovot Ulpanim">Rechovot Ulpanim</A></STRONG></FONT><P>
<FONT SIZE=+1>T</FONT>here are a few ulpanim in Rechovot, but they are coordinated through the 
Rakezet Ulpanim (Hadassa) at the Ministry of Absorption - Tel: 08-9452413, Fax: 09-
9452413.  An oleh must go through this procedure first.  There is a rolling admission 
whereby a new class is started at times when there are enough people to fill a class.  
The most popular ulpan is in Beit Hatarbut, Rechov Habanim 11, Rechovot. Tel: 08-492239. Please note: To register one must go through the Ministry of Absorption, 
otherwise, a person will not be accepted.<P>
