<BODY BACKGROUND="bgrnd.jpg" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#0000FF" VLINK="#800080" ALINK="#FF0000">
<IMG SRC="logo-sm.gif" WIDTH=394 HEIGHT=48><HR>
<UL>
<CENTER><FONT SIZE=+3><EM><STRONG>SCHOOL AND GANIM REGISTRATION<BR>AACI INFORMATION SHEET</STRONG></EM></FONT></CENTER><HR WIDTH=60% ALIGN=center>
<CENTER><FONT SIZE=+2><STRONG>1996</STRONG></FONT></CENTER><P>
Most school registration is done through the Education Departments of 
the individual municipalities. The educational department will let you 
know if you need to register your child at the school directly or with 
them.  Tourists coming for Sabbatical year to Israel must register 
through the municipalities and pay a charge or fee that Israeli or 
Olim children do not pay. Check with the individual municipality what 
the charges are. In general, these charges go up annually.<P>
Most municipalities require some of or all of the following documents 
for the registration process:<P>
<UL>
<LI>"Teudat Zehut" of both parents, or passport numbers
<LI>Birth certificate and birth date of child
<LI>School records of child
<LI>Inoculation records of child
<LI>Rental or purchase contract of residence of family
<LI>Last report cards
<LI>"Teudat Oleh" of family
<LI>Details of other children in the family
<LI>Year of birth of parents, occupation etc.
<LI>For ganim or first grade children, municipal form, mailed to the parents.
<LI>Any other document requested.
</UL><P> 
Check with the office before going in to register your child.<P>
