<HEAD><TITLE>AACI - Informaton for the Deaf</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="bgrnd.jpg" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#0000FF" VLINK="#800080" ALINK="#FF0000">
<IMG SRC="logo-sm.gif" WIDTH=394 HEIGHT=48><HR>
<UL>
<CENTER><FONT SIZE=+3><EM><STRONG>Schools & Infomation for the 
Deaf<BR>AACI Information Sheet</STRONG></EM></FONT></CENTER><HR WIDTH=60% ALIGN=center><P>
Schooling and programs are divided according to age.  In most cases 
children are integrated into regular classrooms.<P>
"Micha" the organization that works with the deaf. They have material 
in English and Hebrew.  Their school has a kindergarten and nursery 
program and deals with children up to age 6 / 7.  Micha also has 
information on organizations that deal with the older children 
and adults throughout Israel.<P>

<STRONG>Micha - Tel Aviv</STRONG><BR>National Council ("Moatza artzit")<BR>22 Reading St,. Ramat Aviv, Tel Aviv 69020<BR>Tel: 03-6994777,  Fax:03-6999477, C/O Rachel Zohar<P>

<STRONG>Micha - Jerusalem</STRONG><BR>Rechov Rabbi Akiba 4<BR>Jerusalem<BR>Tel: 02-6250034  /No Fax<BR>POB 2029, Jerusalem 91020<P>

<STRONG>Another contact is:</STRONG><BR>Beit Helen Keller, Israel Deaf Association<BR>13 Shderot yad Binyamin<BR>Yad Eliyahu, Tel Aviv<BR>Tel: 03-7303355,  Fax: 03-7396419<P>

<STRONG>Services for Deaf Adults:</STRONG><BR>Shema<BR>Rehov Plitei Hasefer 30A<BR>Tel Aviv<BR>Tel: 03-5715656<BR>Fax:03-571-2017

Prepared by: Cindy Breakstone
Updated: January 1996
</UL>

