<HEAD><TITLE>AACI - Information sheet</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="bgrnd.jpg" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#0000FF" VLINK="#800080" ALINK="#FF0000">
<IMG SRC="logo-sm.gif" WIDTH=394 HEIGHT=48><HR>
<UL>
<CENTER><FONT SIZE=+3><EM><STRONG>AACI Information Sheet</STRONG></EM></FONT></CENTER>

<H3>Bezek Update
<BR>
1996
</H3>

There have been several changes in phone numbers over the last year or two in Israel, but there are more changes scheduled for this year. Bezek has told us that by the end of 1996, all phone numbers in Israel will be 7 digits.<P>
The additional digit will be added to the beginning of the telephone number. This will advance Bezek's telephone system technologically. If you receive any information sheet with telephone numbers on it, make sure you also look at this telephone update.<P>

According to the Bezek Information sheet in our hands, the following schedule of changes have taken or will take place:
<P>
04 area
<P>
7\11\95
<P>
Already added to the beginning of telephone numbers starting with 2,3,4,5,6,7, was the digit 8.

<P>
09 area
<P>
23\10\96
<P>
Add the digit 8 to the beginning of the telephone numbers starting with 3,6,8.<BR>
Add the digit 7 to the beginning of the telephone numbers starting with 4,9.<BR>
Add the digit 9 to the beginning of the telephone numbers starting with 5.<P>


03 area
<P>
3\96
<P>
In Bat Yam, add the digit 6 to the beginning of the telephone numbers starting with 58.<P>


03 area
<P>
6-8\96
<P>
In Holon, telephone numbers that begin with 88, will be changed to 651.
<P>
08 area
<P>
12\12\95
<P>
Already added to the beginning of telephone numbers that start with 5,6, was the digit 8.
<BR>
Already added to the beginning of telephone numbers that start with 2,3,4,7, was the digit 9.
<P>

06 area<P>

17\12\96<P>

Add the digit 6 to the beginning of telephone numbers that start with 2,3,4,5,7,8,9.  <P>

02 area<P>

6\8\96<P>

Add the digit 5 to the beginning of the telephone numbers that start with 3,6,8.<BR>

Add the digit 6 to the beginning of telephone numbers that start with 2,4,7.
<P>

07 area<P>

2\7\96<P>

Add the digit 6 to the beginning of telephone numbers that start with 2,3,4,5,7,8<BR>

Add the digit 9 to the beginning of telephone numbers that start with 9.<P>



<B>Tel 177-022-0707 for a Hebrew Bezek information recording.</B><P>
<I>Translated by Cindy Breakstone</I><P><hr>
