<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>AACI - Travel Experience</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="bgrnd.jpg" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#0000FF" VLINK="#800080" ALINK="#FF0000">
<IMG SRC="logo-sm.gif" WIDTH=394 HEIGHT=48><HR>
<UL>
<CENTER><FONT SIZE=+3><EM><STRONG>PARENTS OF NORTH AMERICAN ISRAELIS</STRONG></EM></FONT></CENTER><HR WIDTH=60% ALIGN=center><P>




PNAI is an all-volunteer, non-profit, non-fundraising organization.  Besides 
parents, we also welcome as members children, siblings, grandparents, and other 
close relative of North American Israelis.<P>

Formed in 1974 by a core of 12 families in the NYC area led by Nahum and Sylvia 
Weissman (z"l), our purpose, then and now, is to be a strong bridge of support to 
our children, grandchildren and close relatives in Israel, to the State of Israel and 
among ourselves.  Our membership is diverse regarding religious practices, 
political preferences, socio-economic status, etc., and we never impose a uniform 
outlook.  We are bound together by a common hope and concern for our families' 
future.<P>

PNAI provides a platform for sharing the interest and excitement of having family 
members actively participating in the challenging task of building a Jewish State.  
It also offers support and a sympathetic shoulder to lean on when separation from 
loved ones  becomes too difficult to deal with alone.  Even though many of us are 
involved in other organizations, our special group has a tie that binds us in an 
exclusive way.<P>

We strive to keep thoroughly well-informed about all issues concerning Israel. We 
are working to assist our children, and all olim, to achieve successful absorption, 
surmount the difficult problems of housing, make travel to and from Israel easier, 
to promote the increased purchase of Israeli products, and establish landsmanshaft 
groups in Israel in cooperation with the Association of Americans and Canadians in 
Israel (AACI).  The AACI also administers our interest-free Emergency <A HREF="loan&mor.htm">Loan Fund</A> 
available to offspring of members.<P>

The name and address of any prospective member may be sent to:<BR>
<address>
Leonard Eisenberg<BR>
International Vice President of Membership<BR>
13618 Whippet Way West<BR>
Delray Beach FL<BR>
33484<BR>
Tel: (561) 499-3216<br>
Fax:  (561) 498-0552<BR>
E-mail <A HREF="mailto:lene2@fau.campus.mci.net">lene2@fau.campus.mci.net</A><BR>
</address><P>
                                    


