<HEAD><TITLE>AACI - 31st Biennial Convention</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="bgrnd.jpg" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#0000FF" VLINK="#800080" ALINK="#FF0000">
<IMG SRC="logo-sm.gif" WIDTH=394 HEIGHT=48><HR>
<UL>
<CENTER><FONT SIZE=+2><EM><STRONG>AACI<BR>31st BIENNIAL CONVENTION<BR>SUNDAY - MONDAY, MAY 12 - 13, 1996</STRONG></EM></FONT></CENTER><HR WIDTH=60% ALIGN=center><P>
AACI will be holding its 31st Biennial Convention at<A 
HREF="http://www.jer1.co.il/tourism/lavi/index.html"> Kibbutz 
Lavi</A> 
situated in the heart of the scenic Lower Galilee, which is 
steeped in Jewish History and tradition. In this pastoral atmosphere, 
AACI's delegates from Kiryat Shmonah to Eilat, will discuss:<P>
<CENTER><STRONG>TOLERANCE & DEMOCRACY</STRONG></CENTER>
in an atmosphere of soul searching and civility.<P>
With the assassination of Prime Minister Yitzhak Rabin, z"l, 
fresh in our minds, and the upcoming  elections upon us, some of 
the country's leading thinkers will join AACI members to deliberate 
the issues of:<P>
<CENTER><STRONG>TOLERANCE & DEMOCRACY</STRONG></CENTER>
will be deliberated with us by some of the country's leading thinkers.<P>
<CENTER><STRONG>~~ JOIN US ~~</STRONG></CENTER>
as we discuss AACI business, elect our new officers, and examine issues 
relevant to the future of our organization.<P>
Renew old acquaintances and make new friends. Enjoy spectacular 
vistas, a guided tour, delicious meals, and a Gala Dinner with 
the American and Canadian Ambassadors. Also available to you are 
the fresh clean air of the Galilee, an indoor heated swimming p
ool, and the warm hospitality of Kibbutz Lavi and AACI.<P>
