<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>AACI - Aliyah Check List</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="bgrnd.jpg" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#0000FF" VLINK="#800080" ALINK="#FF0000">
<IMG SRC="logo-sm.gif" WIDTH=394 HEIGHT=48><HR>
<UL>
<CENTER><FONT SIZE=+3><EM><STRONG>AACI - Aliyah Check List</STRONG></EM></FONT></CENTER><HR WIDTH=60% ALIGN=center>
<CENTER><FONT SIZE=+1><STRONG>Pre-Aliyah Hints - Making Aliyah from North America through the Israel Aliyah Offices Abroad:</STRONG></FONT>
<BR><STRONG>1996</STRONG></CENTER><P>
<FONT SIZE=+1>T</FONT>his has been prepared using ideas that appeared on 
TACHLIS, from AACI Know-how, and from other past Olim. Time frames may 
VARY from person to person. Make sure that you are either in touch with 
the Israel Aliyah Center Abroad closest to you or your Regional AACI 
office for updates in information as regulations and policy can change!<P>
 <P ALIGN=right><EM>- Cindy Breakstone</EM></P>
<STRONG>What to do at first:</STRONG><P>
<UL>
<LI> Join one or more Aliyah Organizations.
<LI>Get on the list for Chugei Aliyah at Israel Aliyah Centers.
<LI>Begin learning or polishing up your Hebrew. There are Ulpanim abroad.
<LI> Decide on a tentative Aliyah target date.
<LI>Make an appointment with the Shaliach at the Israel Aliyah Center 
closest to you, and, if ready, open up an Aliyah File.
<LI>Explore <A HREF="employ.htm">employment opportunities</A> in Israel 
by having your Shaliach send your resume to AACI, Overseas Employment 
Office, National AACI.
<LI>Plan a possible pilot trip if you feel it will assist you and your 
spouse explore employment options.
<LI>Get Pre-Aliyah Check list from Shaliach on procedure of making 
Aliyah through the Israel Aliyah Center abroad. In general, it takes 
at least 3 months, and, possibly much longer, to complete this Aliyah 
Processing through the Israel Aliyah Center abroad. SO DON'T WAIT 
TO THE LAST MINUTE!
<LI>Take out AACI Overseas Membership if you haven't done so already!
</UL><P>
<STRONG>The following documents may be requested from you :</STRONG><P>
<UL>
<LI>2 Aliyah questionnaires filled out.
<LI>Photos, ask Shaliach # of adult, # of each child. 
<LI>Proof of Judaism.
<LI>Copies of all Passports, all pages.
<LI>Proof of residence outside of Israel.
<LI>Teudat Oleh, if ever had one.
<LI>Student Authority application, if relevant.
<LI>Proof of study in Israel on recognized program, if relevant.
<LI>Ex-spouse waiver, Divorce Agreement, "Get", and child custody papers, 
if relevant.
<LI>One parent family form, if relevant.
<LI>Adoption papers, if relevant.
<LI>Resume.
<LI>Medical records; back health records may be requested.
<LI>Marriage and birth certificates of children.
<LI>Conversion Certificate, if relevant.
<LI>Civil marriage certificate and "Ketuba".
<LI>"Katin Chozer" Statement or "Yalid Chul", Israeli born abroad statement, 
if relevant.
<LI>Report of any court verdict or crime, if relevant.
<LI>Money to open up an Aliyah File.
<LI>Note:
Other documents or evaluations may be requested of you.<BR>
Once you have provided the correct documentation, the Israel Aliyah 
Center will forward your file to Jerusalem, and a response to your 
application can be expected in 1-1 1\2 - 3 months.
</UL><P>
<STRONG>One year prior to Aliyah</STRONG><P>
<UL>
<LI>Have a Shaliach make reservations in an Absorption Center if you 
are entitled, and this is what you chose.
<LI>Discuss with various Realtors when you should put the house on 
the market.
</UL><P>
<STRONG>Six Months prior to Aliyah:</STRONG><P>
<UL>
<LI>Most past olim say by six months prior to Aliyah you should 
begin process of selling your home.
<LI>Start to check Shipping costs.  Contact AACI insurance for marine 
insurance estimates. Tel 1-800-922-2465. Get other AACINSURANCE 
information for living in Israel.
</UL><P>
<STRONG>Four Months prior to Aliyah:</STRONG><P>
<UL>
<LI>Make sure that passports of each member in the family are up to date.
<LI>Make EL AL reservations with advice from your Shaliach.
<LI>Start comparing prices of appliances and furniture that you wish 
to ship to Israel by making appointments with appliance dealers and 
going to furniture stores, and other stores !!!
<LI>Get estimates from Shippers in your home.  Choose Shipper.
</UL><P>
<STRONG>Three Months Prior to Aliyah:</STRONG><P>
<UL>
<LI>Confirm reservations in Absorption Center through Shaliach.
<LI>Renew American and Canadian Driver's licenses if they expire within 
one year.
<LI>Order any item by mail that are being purchased to take to Israel.
<LI>Check with the Shaliach to see what paperwork is still necessary to 
be completed.
</UL><P>
<STRONG>Two Months Prior to Aliyah:</STRONG><P>
<UL>
<LI>Medical Examination Reports must be filed with the Shaliach. All 
adults and children over 12 need medical exams. Obtain letters from 
pediatrician of children under 12 stating that children are in good 
health, are fit to immigrate to Israel, and have up to date 
vaccinations. Double check that there have been no changes with your 
Shaliach.  Medicals can be submitted 6 months prior to Oleh visa 
request, but will be required to redo if more than 6 months has elapsed. 
<LI>Make several photos of each adult and child. (Suggested six for 
adults, four for children.)
<LI>Finalize pick up date with Shipper if hasn't been done already.
<LI>Separate items going to Israel. Separate those items if sending 
a split shipment, that is, those things going for long term storage 
once in Israel, and those things for temporary housing. Also separate 
those items for airplane.  Make sure that those items not being sent 
to Israel are separated as well such as : things to be sold at Tag 
Sales, things to be given away to charity and relatives etc.  
<LI>Obtain visa applications and air fare loan applications at 
Israel Aliyah Center.
<LI>Apply for visas at Israeli Consulate.
</UL><P>
<STRONG>One Month prior to Aliyah:</STRONG><P>
<UL>
<LI>Finalize with appliance dealer all appliances being sent to  
lift. ( Storage is most likely available with Shipper.)
<LI>Shop for all non appliances purchases being sent in the lift 
such as linens, pots, pans, dishes, clothes etc.
<LI>Bring visas and completed air fare loan applications to 
Israel Aliyah Center; when ready, vouchers for air fare should 
be picked up and hand delivered to EL AL to pay for seats. Make sure 
that there have been no changes in procedures at Israel Aliyah Center.
<LI>Officially notify Aliyah Center of departure date, and make 
sure Shaliach will send your departure details to the American 
Desk who will then notify AACI of arrival details in Israel. 
With this information received by AACI, an AACI volunteer will try 
to meet you at the airport to assist you.
<LI>Notify other Aliyah organizations of your departure date.
<LI>Obtain " Michtav Klita" from Israel Aliyah Center.
<LI>Arrange for change of address to be sent to newspaper and 
magazine subscriptions, bank statements, visa bills and other 
bills. Cut off electricity, telephone etc. Arrange for forwarding of 
all mail.
<LI>Obtain from local Board of Elections application forms for 
absentee ballot on a permanent basis. Fill out and mail.
<LI>Obtain from local Motor Vehicles any required change of address 
forms for car owners and driver's license holders. Fill out and mail.
<LI>Obtain letter from your car insurance company that you have a 
clean driving record, IF YOU DO !
<LI>Give someone close who is staying in North America Power of 
Attorney just in case.
<LI>Make sure that your lawyer and accountant know your Aliyah 
plans and that they give you relevant information on the implications 
of your move.
<LI>Xerox copies of the following documents for your whole family 
and bring originals and copies with you on Aliyah in your hand luggage. 
Do not put in your lift :
</UL><P>
<STRONG>Xerox:</STRONG><P>
<UL>
<LI>All your passports for members of whole family, old and current 
ones, birth certificates, dental records, medical records, school 
records, diplomas, wills," Ketuba"," Get", Adoption papers, other 
legal documents, medical prescriptions, driver licenses, visas, 
"Michtav Maavar" etc.   
<LI>Get rid of things that you are either giving  to charity or 
to relatives.
</UL><P>
<STRONG>At least 10 days prior to Shipping, prior to Shipping Pick 
Up:</STRONG><P>
<UL>
<LI>Begin to prepare packing lists. Include serial numbers of appliances.
<LI>Pack all items for the plane. ( Each paying passenger over 2, 
is entitled to 3 suitcases or cartons each having total linear 
dimensions  (height + length + width) of up to 62 inches and a weight of 
70 pounds, and one carry on having total linear dimensions of up 
to 39 inches.) Re check that these regulations haven't changed.
<LI>Pack already separated items for split lift, that is, term 
storage, temporary housing.  Arrange for marine insurance. Arrange 
pick up of Shipment.
</UL><P>
<STRONG>Two weeks prior to Aliyah</STRONG><P>
<UL>
<LI>Confirm reservations on EL AL. Arrange for special meals, children's 
needs etc.
<LI>Get fresh medical prescriptions that will hold you for a while 
once your in Israel.
<LI>Get ready for move out of the house.
</UL><P>
<STRONG>One day prior to Aliyah:</STRONG><P>
<FONT SIZE=+1>I</FONT>f living in NY area, one can drop off 
luggage  (OTHER THAN CARRY ON BAGS), with EL AL in Brooklyn if 
desired ( between 7 p.m. and 10 p.m. if leaving Monday through 
Friday, ( if leaving on Saturday night drop off on Thursday night; if 
leaving on Sunday drop off one hour after Shabbat ends to midnight. 
Remember to check this with EL-AL.<P>
<STRONG>Attached is the CHECK LIST from the Israel Aliyah Center:</STRONG><P>
<CENTER><TABLE CELLSPACING=5>
<CAPTION ALIGN=top><CENTER><FONT SIZE=+2><EM><STRONG>ALIYAH TIK CHECKLIST</STRONG></EM></FONT></CENTER></CAPTION>
<TR><TH>Requested</TH><TH>Received</TH><TH></TH></TR>
<TR><TD>________</TD><TD>________</TD><TD>Questionnaire (2 Identical Originals)</TD></TR>
<TR><TD>________</TD><TD>________</TD><TD>Photographs</TD></TR>
<TR><TD>________</TD><TD>________</TD><TD>Proof of Judaism</TD></TR>
<TR><TD>________</TD><TD>________</TD><TD>Entry - Exit Forms, Copies of all passports<BR>(all pages with stamps)</TD></TR>
<TR><TD>________</TD><TD>________</TD><TD>Medicals</TD></TR>
<TR><TD>________</TD><TD>________</TD><TD>Documents for continuous stay abroad</TD></TR>
<TR><TD>________</TD><TD>________</TD><TD>Resume</TD></TR>
<TR><TD>________</TD><TD>________</TD><TD>Certificate (Marriage, Birth)</TD></TR>
<TR><TD>________</TD><TD>________</TD><TD>$60 (single) $80 (couple +) Check made<BR>out to Israel Aliyah Center</TD></TR>
</TABLE></CENTER>
</UL>

