<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>AACI - Professional Licensing Requirements</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="bgrnd.jpg" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#0000FF" VLINK="#800080" ALINK="#FF0000">
<IMG SRC="logo-sm.gif" WIDTH=394 HEIGHT=48><HR>
<UL>
<CENTER><FONT SIZE=+3><EM><STRONG>LICENSING AND RECOGNITION:<BR>INFORMATION & PROCEDURES</STRONG></EM></FONT></CENTER><HR WIDTH=60% ALIGN=center><P>
Important documents should always be brought with you to Israel in 
your hand luggage.  Bring the originals and plenty of  notarized copies.  
Original documents should be used for presentation purposes only.  
NEVER give original documents to anyone!!  Also bring plenty of passport 
photos. <H2><A NAME="Index">Index</A></H2>
<A HREF="#ACCOUNTANTS">ACCOUNTANTS</A><BR>
<A HREF="#ACTUARIES">ACTUARIES</A><BR>
<A HREF="#ARCHITECTS">ARCHITECTS</A><BR>
<A HREF="#DENTISTS">DENTISTS</A><BR>
<A HREF="#DENTAL PARA-PROFESSIONALS">DENTAL PARA-PROFESSIONALS</A><BR>
<A HREF="#ELECTRICIANS">ELECTRICIANS</A><BR>
<A HREF="#ENGINEERS">ENGINEERS</A><BR>
<A HREF="#LAWYERS">LAWYERS</A><BR>
<A HREF="#MEDICAL PARA PROFESSIONALS">MEDICAL PARA PROFESSIONALS</A><BR>
<A HREF="#NURSES">NURSES</A><BR>
<A HREF="#OPTOMETRISTS">OPTOMETRISTS</A><BR>
<A HREF="#PHARMACISTS">PHARMACISTS</A><BR>
<A HREF="#PHYSICAL THERAPISTS">PHYSICAL THERAPISTS</A><BR>
<A HREF="#PHYSICIANS">PHYSICIANS</A><BR>
<A HREF="#PSYCHOLOGISTS">PSYCHOLOGISTS</A><BR>
<A HREF="#SOCIAL WORKERS">SOCIAL WORKERS</A><BR>
<A HREF="#TOUR GUIDES">TOUR GUIDES</A><BR>
<A HREF="#VETERINARIANS">VETERINARIANS</A><P>
<CENTER><FONT SIZE=+2><EM><STRONG><A NAME="ACCOUNTANTS">ACCOUNTANTS</A></STRONG></EM></FONT></CENTER>
<HR WIDTH=60% ALIGN=center NOSHADE><P>
One must obtain an Israeli CPA license to work as a certified accountant 
in Israel.  This is done through the Auditors Council.  CPAs from the US 
and Canada are exempt from all exams except for Laws of Bodies Corporate; 
Taxation; Commercial, Labor and other Laws.  Exams are mostly multiple 
choice with a few essays.  The exam may be taken in English.  Olim 
accountants who are not CPAs must take additional exams.  Exams are 
given twice a year, in the spring and fall, and registration takes 
place a few months beforehand.  Preparatory courses are given by 
the Ministry of Absorption and by private accountants.  It is possible 
that in the future a Hebrew proficiency exam may also be required.  
Depending on one's work experience, a minimum of a six month internship 
is also necessary.<P>
Be sure to bring with you your original license plus clear copies, 
a letter from your licensing body indicating that your license is in 
good standing and specifying the period of your work experience, 
letters of recommendation from employers detailing your work experience, 
and a curriculum vitae.<P>
The Institute of CPAs is a voluntary body for the advancement of 
the accounting profession and has a committee to assist olim.<P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING=20>
<TR VALIGN=top><TD>Auditors Council<BR>Clal Building, 97 Jaffa Rd<BR>POB 2180<BR>91021 Jerusalem<BR>Phone:  02-6209484/5/6/7/8<BR>Fax:  02-6209489</TD>
<TD>Institute of Certified Public Accountants<BR>1 Montifiore Street<BR>POB  29281<BR>61292  Tel Aviv<BR>Phone:  03-516-1114<BR>Fax:   03-510-3105</TD></TR>
</TABLE><P>
<A HREF="#Index">Return To Index</A><P>

<CENTER><FONT SIZE=+2><EM><STRONG><A NAME="ACTUARIES">ACTUARIES</A></STRONG></EM></FONT></CENTER>
<HR WIDTH=60% ALIGN=center NOSHADE><P>
All information regarding the licensing procedure can be obtained from:<P>
Association of Actuaries<BR>
1 Goldberg Street<BR>
65784  Tel Aviv<BR>
Phone:  03-566-1155  (ask for Aguda)<P>
<A HREF="#Index">Return To Index</A><P>

<CENTER><FONT SIZE=+2><EM><STRONG><A NAME="ARCHITECTS">ARCHITECTS</A></STRONG></EM></FONT></CENTER>
<HR WIDTH=60% ALIGN=center NOSHADE><P>
To be registered as an architect one must be recognized by the Director 
of Licensing and Registration of Engineers and Architects.   You are 
required to hold a degree from a recognized institution of higher learning.  
Generally speaking, recognition of one's credentials is sufficient in 
order to practice in Israel.  However, additional evaluation procedures 
may be implemented if you hold a diploma that is not from a recognized 
institution of higher learning or if you have a diploma in a specialty 
not recognized in Israel.  You can apply to the Registrar from abroad 
to clarify your status.<P>
To be licensed as an architect you must have worked in your field 
for at least three consecutive years after completing your studies 
and must provide proof of such employment.  Employment outside Israel 
is recognized but it is necessary to have one year's work experience in 
Israel before being granted a license.  If you worked for less than 
three years you must complete the remainder in Israel;  your experience 
outside of Israel will count if you submit your application within one  
year of your aliyah.<P>


Be sure to bring with you your original diploma and notarized copies, 
a complete transcript of courses taken and documented proof of your 
employment history.<P>
The Association of Engineers and Architects is a professional organization 
with information on the field in Israel;  it also publishes a professional 
journal.<P>

Director of Licensing and Registration of Engineers and Architects<BR>
(Rishui VeRishum HaMehandesim  VeHaAdrichalim)<BR>
86 Derech Petach Tikva<BR>
POB  36049<BR>
61360  Tel Aviv<BR>
Phone:  03-563-4184/5<BR>
Fax:   03-563-4170<P>

The Association of Engineers and Architects<BR>
(Lishkat HaMehandissim VeAdrichalim)<BR>
Beit HaMehandes<BR>
Rechov Dizengoff 200<BR>
POB 3082<BR>
61030  Tel Aviv<BR>
Phone:  03-524-0274<BR>
Fax:  03-523-5993<P>
<A HREF="#Index">Return To Index</A><P>

<CENTER><FONT SIZE=+2><EM><STRONG><A NAME="DENTISTS">DENTISTS</A></STRONG></EM></FONT></CENTER>
<HR WIDTH=60% ALIGN=center NOSHADE><P>
All dentists must pass a licensing exam in order to practice in Israel.  
There are no exemptions.  The exam is given twice a year, in February/March, 
and in September/October.  It is possible to take the exam in English.  
Preparatory courses are offered before each exam.  One may take the 
exam before making aliyah but must have already opened an aliyah file; 
one must make aliyah within two years of the exam date to be granted 
a license based on that exam.<P>
You must bring with you your dental diploma, dental license, and a resume.<P>
All inquiries and requests for applications should be directed to:<P>

Dr. A. M. Kellman<BR>
Director of Dental Health<BR>
Ministry of Health<BR>
20 King David St.<BR>
POB  1176<BR>
91010 Jerusalem<BR>
Phone:  02-6247173, 6247471<BR>
Fax:  02-6259218<P>
<A HREF="#Index">Return To Index</A><P>

<CENTER><FONT SIZE=+2><EM><STRONG><A NAME="DENTAL PARA-PROFESSIONALS">DENTAL PARA-PROFESSIONALS</A></STRONG></EM></FONT></CENTER>
<HR WIDTH=60% ALIGN=center NOSHADE><P>
Dental technicians, hygienists (shineni'it), and assistants (saya'at) 
must apply for certification to the local Ministry of Health.  You 
must submit your diploma and other relevant work documents.  After a 
review of your application and documents the office will determine if 
you must take an exam or be granted certification immediately.<P>
<A HREF="#Index">Return To Index</A><P>

<CENTER><FONT SIZE=+2><EM><STRONG><A NAME="ELECTRICIANS">ELECTRICIANS</A></STRONG></EM></FONT></CENTER>
<HR WIDTH=60% ALIGN=center NOSHADE><P>
One must apply for a license to be recognized as an electrician.<P>
You must bring with you your diploma, certificates and licenses (originals 
plus notarized copies), a resume listing your work history and a 
letter of recommendation from a past employer.<P>
Applications are made to:<P>

Ministry of Labor<BR>
Department of  Licensing of Electricians<BR>
Rechov Jaffe 30<BR>
Jerusalem<BR>
Phone:  02-6294911<BR>
Fax:  02-6294929<P>
<A HREF="#Index">Return To Index</A><P>

<CENTER><FONT SIZE=+2><EM><STRONG><A NAME="ENGINEERS">ENGINEERS</A></STRONG></EM></FONT></CENTER>
<HR WIDTH=60% ALIGN=center NOSHADE><P>
To be registered as an engineer one must be recognized by the Director 
of Licensing and Registration of Engineers and Architects.   You are 
required to hold a degree from a recognized institution of higher learning.  
Generally speaking, recognition of one's credentials is sufficient in 
order to practice in Israel.  However, additional evaluation procedures 
may be implemented if you hold a diploma that is not from a recognized 
institution of higher learning or if you have a diploma in a specialty 
not recognized in Israel.  You can apply to the Registrar from abroad 
to clarify your status.<P>
To be licensed as an engineer you must have worked in your field for 
at least three consecutive years after completing your studies and must 
provide proof of such employment.  Employment outside Israel is recognized 
but it is necessary to have one year's work experience in Israel before 
being granted a license.  If you worked for less than three years you 
must complete the remainder in Israel;  your experience outside of Israel 
will count if you submit your application within one  year of your aliyah.<P>
Be sure to bring with you your original diploma and notarized copies, 
a complete transcript of courses taken and documented proof of your 
employment history.<P>
The Association of Engineers and Architects is a professional 
organization with information on the field in Israel;  it also publishes 
a professional journal.<P>

Director of Licensing and Registration of Engineers and Architects<BR>
(Rishui VeRishum HaMehandesim  VeHaAdrichalim)<BR>
86 Derech Petach Tikva<BR>
POB  36049<BR>
61360  Tel Aviv<BR>
Phone:  03-563-4184/5<BR>
Fax:   03-563-4170<P>

The Association of Engineers and Architects<BR>
(Lishkat HaMehandissim VeAdrichalim)<BR>
Beit HaMehandes<BR>
Rechov Dizengoff 200<BR>
POB 3082<BR>
61030  Tel Aviv<BR>
Phone:  03-524-0274<BR>
Fax:  03-523-5993<P>
<A HREF="#Index">Return To Index</A><P>

<CENTER><FONT SIZE=+2><EM><STRONG><A NAME="LAWYERS">LAWYERS</A></STRONG></EM></FONT></CENTER>
<HR WIDTH=60% ALIGN=center NOSHADE><P>
To be admitted to the Israel Bar, olim lawyers must have their legal 
credentials recognized, pass examinations, do an internship and be 
residents of Israel.<P>
Applications are submitted to the Israel Bar Association.  You must bring 
with you your original degree, diploma, certificates, transcripts and a 
resume, plus notarized copies of these documents.<P>
Examinations are held twice a year, in the winter and summer.  All questions 
are in Hebrew but you may answer in English.  Most North American lawyers 
can be exempted from the following exams:  Torts, Criminal Law, Commercial 
Law and Commercial Law B (except for tax law).  Preparatory courses are 
offered by the Israel Bar and privately.<P>
Internship ("Articles") may be from 6 to 18 months, at the discretion of 
the Israel Bar.<P>

Israel Bar Association<BR>
1 Rechov Chopin<BR>
92190  Jerusalem<BR>
Phone:  02-5660271<P>

Bar Preparatory Course (in English)<BR>
David Seville<BR>
Ben Maimon 24<BR>
Jerusalem<BR>
Phone:  02-5669263<BR>
F:  02-5669265<P>
<A HREF="#Index">Return To Index</A><P>

<CENTER><FONT SIZE=+2><EM><STRONG><A NAME="MEDICAL PARA PROFESSIONALS">MEDICAL PARA PROFESSIONALS</A></STRONG></EM></FONT></CENTER>
<HR WIDTH=60% ALIGN=center NOSHADE><P>

The following professions are recognized in Israel:<P>
Chiropractors<BR>
Dental Hygienists/Assistants<BR>
Dieticians<BR>
Electro-Physiology Technicians<BR>
Expressive Therapists (music, art, dance)<BR>
Laboratory Technicians<BR>
Nuclear Medicine Technicians<BR>
Occupational Therapists<BR>
Physical Therapists<BR>
Podiatrists<BR>
Respiratory Therapists<BR>
Speech Therapists<BR>
Ultrasound Technicians<BR>
X-Ray Technicians<P>
You must apply to the local Ministry of Health for a Certificate of 
Recognition.  You will either receive this Certificate or be informed of 
further requirements.<P>
You should bring with you your diploma, transcript, licenses or 
certifications, and work documents.<P>
The following professional organizations may be helpful:<P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING=10>
<TR VALIGN=top><TD>The Association of Chiropractors in 
Israel<BR>c/o David Greenblatt
<BR>The Chiropratic Center
<BR>Rechov Caspi 20
<BR>Jerusalem
<BR>Phone: 02-6717464</TD>
<TD>Association of Physical Therapists<BR>
Vaad Hapoel<BR>
Rechov Arlozorov 93<BR>
Tel Aviv<BR>
Phone: 03-6431889</TD></TR>
<TR VALIGN=top><TD>Association of Occupational Therapists<BR>
Vaad Hapoel<BR>
Rechov Arlozorov 93<BR>
Tel Aviv<BR>
Phone: 03-6431266</TD>
<TD>HaAguda LeKlina'ai Tikshoret<BR>
(Speech Therapists)<BR>
Rechov Redding 23<BR>
Ramat Aviv<BR>
Phone: 03-699-4777</TD></TR>
</TABLE>
<A HREF="#Index">Return To Index</A><P>

<CENTER><FONT SIZE=+2><EM><STRONG><A NAME="NURSES">NURSES</A></STRONG></EM></FONT></CENTER>
<HR WIDTH=60% ALIGN=center NOSHADE><P>
All olim nurses must pass a licensing exam to be recognized in Israel.  
You can start the application process before aliyah.<P>
You should bring with you your diploma, transcript of courses, licenses, 
resume, and letters from previous employers indicating your work history.<P>
For information and applications contact:<P>
Drora Ehrlich<BR>
Director of Nursing Division<BR>
Ministry of Health<BR>
2 Ben Tabai Street<BR>
03591  Jerusalem<BR>
Phone:  02-6705903<BR>
Fax:  02-6781456<P>

Additional job information is available from:<P>
National Association of Nurses<BR>
43 Arlozorov Street<BR>
POB 303<BR>
61002  Tel Aviv<BR>
Phone:  03-692-1462<BR>
Fax:   03-691-7460<P>
<A HREF="#Index">Return To Index</A><P>

<CENTER><FONT SIZE=+2><EM><STRONG><A NAME="OPTOMETRISTS">OPTOMETRISTS</A></STRONG></EM></FONT></CENTER>
<HR WIDTH=60% ALIGN=center NOSHADE><P>
Optometrists must now pass an examination, given in July and December.  
Information and applications can be obtained from:<P>

Ministry of Health<BR>
Medical Professions Dept.<BR>
2 Ben Tabai<BR>
93591  Jerusalem<BR>
Phone:  02-6705705<P>

Optometrists Association<BR>
Rechov Nachmani  53<BR>
Tel Aviv<BR>
03-560-3856<P>
<A HREF="#Index">Return To Index</A><P>

<CENTER><FONT SIZE=+2><EM><STRONG><A NAME="PHARMACISTS">PHARMACISTS</A></STRONG></EM></FONT></CENTER>
<HR WIDTH=60% ALIGN=center NOSHADE><P>
All olim pharmacists must take a licensing exam.  There are no exemptions.  
The exam is given in the winter and the summer and can be taken in 
English.  Preparatory courses are given before each exam.<P>
You should have your diploma, license and documentation of work 
experience.<P>
For more information contact:<P>

Ministry of Health<BR>
Dept. of the Medical Professions<BR>
2 Rechov Ben Tabai<BR>
91010  Jerusalem<BR>
Phone:  02-6705705<BR>
Fax:  02-6781465<P>
<A HREF="#Index">Return To Index</A><P>

<CENTER><FONT SIZE=+2><EM><STRONG><A NAME="PHYSICAL THERAPISTS">PHYSICAL THERAPISTS</A></STRONG></EM></FONT></CENTER>
<HR WIDTH=60% ALIGN=center NOSHADE><P>

Association of Physical Therapists<BR>
Vaad Hapoel<BR>
Rechov Arlozorov 93<BR>
Tel Aviv<BR>
Phone:  03-6431889<P>
<A HREF="#Index">Return To Index</A><P>

<CENTER><FONT SIZE=+2><EM><STRONG><A NAME="PHYSICIANS">PHYSICIANS</A></STRONG></EM></FONT></CENTER>
<HR WIDTH=60% ALIGN=center NOSHADE><P>
Physicians who are graduates of US and Canadian medical schools and have 
completed their internships must apply to the Ministry of Health for a 
medical license.  At the present time there is no licensing exam.  
If you have not completed an internship you must do so in Israel and then 
take the licensing exam.<P>
You should bring with you your medical diploma, confirmation of 
internship, licenses to practice and your work record.<P>
Applications are made to:<P>

Dept. of the Medical Professions<BR>
Ministry of Health<BR>
2 Rechov Ben Tabai<BR>
91010  Jerusalem<BR>
Phone:  02-6705820<BR>
Fax:   02-6781465<P>

After receiving a license to practice medicine, one must apply for 
specialty recognition to the Scientific Council.  Records of specialty 
training and places of employment are essential to this process.<P>
Scientific Council of the Medical Association<BR>
Rechov Jabotinsky 35<BR>
Ramat Gan<BR>
Phone:  03-610-0444<BR>
Fax:  03-575-1616<P>
<A HREF="#Index">Return To Index</A><P>

<CENTER><FONT SIZE=+2><EM><STRONG><A NAME="PSYCHOLOGISTS">PSYCHOLOGISTS</A></STRONG></EM></FONT></CENTER>
<HR WIDTH=60% ALIGN=center NOSHADE><P>
Psychologists must register with the Psychologists Registrar to obtain 
official recognition as a psychologist.  Registration is processed 
through the Psychology Registration Committee of the Ministry of 
Health (local branch).<P>
You must have copies of all degrees, transcripts of courses taken for 
all degrees and your thesis.<P>
You can clarify your professional status prior to aliyah  by writing to:<P>

<TABLE CELLSPACING=10>
<TR VALIGN=top><TD>Ministry of Health<BR>
Registration Committee<BR>
Department of Mental Health<BR>
2 Rechov Ben Tabai<BR>
93591 Jerusalem<BR>
Phone:  02-6705705</TD>

<TD>Secretariat<BR>
Council of Psychologists<BR>
36 Rechov Yefet<BR>	
68030  Jaffa<BR>
Phone: 03-6830387</TD></TR>
</TABLE><P>
The professional association advises and supervises beginning and 
oleh psychologists, provides lectures and workshops, distributes 
professional information and represents psychologists in government 
and public institutions.<P>

Israel Psychologists Association (IPA)<BR>
(Histadrut HaPshichologim B'Yisrael)<BR>
2 Rechov HaNeviim<BR>
64356  Tel Aviv<BR>
Phone:  03-523-9393<P>
<A HREF="#Index">Return To Index</A><P>

<CENTER><FONT SIZE=+2><EM><STRONG><A NAME="SOCIAL WORKERS">SOCIAL WORKERS</A></STRONG></EM></FONT></CENTER>
<HR WIDTH=60% ALIGN=center NOSHADE><P>
All social workers must be certified to work in their field.  Diplomas, 
licenses and work records must be submitted to:<P>
Committee on Authorization of Social Workers<BR>
Ministry of Labor and Social Welfare<BR>
10 Yad Harutzim Street<BR>
93420  Jerusalem<BR>
Phone:  02-6708111<BR>
Fax:  02-6731640<P>

Information on work opportunities can be obtained from:<P>
The Israel Association of Social Workers<BR>
93 Arlozorov Street<BR>
62039  Tel Aviv<BR>
Phone:  03-6956482<BR>
Fax:   03-6969292<P>
<A HREF="#Index">Return To Index</A><P>

<CENTER><FONT SIZE=+2><EM><STRONG><A NAME="TOUR GUIDES">TOUR GUIDES</A></STRONG></EM></FONT></CENTER>
<HR WIDTH=60% ALIGN=center NOSHADE><P>
Tour guides are licensed by the Ministry of Tourism and must be graduates 
of the courses offered by the Ministry.  The course is offered at the 
following:<P>

<TABLE CELLSPACING=10>
<TR VALIGN=top><TD>Beit Sefer Letayarut<BR>
Rechov Stricker 19A<BR>
Tel Aviv<BR>
Phone: 03-605-5916<BR>
Fax: 03-544-1764</TD>
<TD>Beit Sefer Letayarut<BR>
Rechov Hillel 2<BR>
Jerusalem<BR>
Phone:  02-6246047</TD></TR>
</TABLE><P>
<A HREF="#Index">Return To Index</A><P>

<CENTER><FONT SIZE=+2><EM><STRONG><A NAME="VETERINARIANS">VETERINARIANS</A></STRONG></EM></FONT></CENTER>
<HR WIDTH=60% ALIGN=center NOSHADE><P>
All olim veterinarians must pass an exam before receiving a license.  The 
exam is offered three times a year and is organized through the 
Hebrew University Koret School of Veterinary Medicine.  The exam is 
given in Hebrew and there are preparatory courses.<P>
You should bring with you all diplomas, licenses and record of employment.<P>
To apply for the exam, contact:<P>

Authority for Veterinary Services<BR>
of the Ministry of Agriculture<BR>
Veterinary Institute<BR>
POB 12<BR>
Beit  Dagam 50200<BR>
Phone: 03-9681555<P>
<A HREF="#Index">Return To Index</A><P>

